You don't know anything.

5
00:00:51,843 --> 00:00:55,263
We should do it in the morning
when her head is clear.

6
00:00:56,639 --> 00:00:58,725
I heard she went on a trip to France

7
00:00:58,850 --> 00:01:00,769
and was possessed by a French spirit.

8
00:01:00,852 --> 00:01:02,353
The spirit of a duchess.

9
00:01:06,357 --> 00:01:09,903
Since she's a noblewoman,
she cares deeply about clothing.

10
00:01:10,111 --> 00:01:11,488
What was it again?

11
00:01:11,613 --> 00:01:12,489
It was...

12
00:01:13,364 --> 00:01:14,657
Yes, that.

13
00:01:15,450 --> 00:01:18,578
Once she's possessed,
she speaks in French.

14
00:01:18,661 --> 00:01:20,246
-So listen carefully.
-Mom.

15
00:01:20,330 --> 00:01:21,539
-Yes.
-Me?

16
00:01:21,623 --> 00:01:23,333
-Yes.
-French?

17
00:01:25,668 --> 00:01:26,753
French?

18
00:01:32,926 --> 00:01:33,927
Here you go.

19
00:01:35,011 --> 00:01:38,264
Your daughter, the wedding, doubt.

20
00:01:38,598 --> 00:01:41,267
Your daughter's marriage, doubt.

21
00:01:44,187 --> 00:01:46,481
Let's see.

22
00:01:48,691 --> 00:01:49,776
She has a lot of friends.

23
00:01:51,111 --> 00:01:53,238
Your daughter, very messy.

24
00:01:54,364 --> 00:01:56,699
Your daughter, very naughty.

25
00:01:58,618 --> 00:02:00,829
Did it just say "naughty"?

26
00:02:01,329 --> 00:02:02,705
That's been my wish all my life.

27
00:02:03,790 --> 00:02:06,334
I can see. I see...

28
00:02:07,168 --> 00:02:10,088
Your daughter's men.
The color of their hair.

29
00:02:10,171 --> 00:02:13,675
The blonde, the blue, the red.

30
00:02:16,177 --> 00:02:17,345
Your daughter's man.

31
00:02:17,512 --> 00:02:20,640
The color of his hair, yellow,
blue, and pink.

32
00:02:22,934 --> 00:02:23,768
What?

33
00:02:23,852 --> 00:02:28,982
Your daughter, the foreigner.
She's dating. Song of love.

34
00:02:30,150 --> 00:02:35,655
Your daughter loves a foreigner. Dating.
Luck is coming.

35
00:02:36,614 --> 00:02:38,575
Very good.

36
00:02:38,825 --> 00:02:39,701
Very good.

37
00:02:40,618 --> 00:02:43,246
I'm tired.

38
00:02:50,461 --> 00:02:52,547
We don't even know our daughter's passcode
to her door lock.

39
00:02:52,630 --> 00:02:54,340
Why bring all these side dishes?

40
00:02:56,009 --> 00:02:58,094
The world has changed so much
for the worse.

41
00:02:58,177 --> 00:02:59,762
-It's a trend.
-You startled me.

42
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:02,640
I told you to give me a signal
before you talk.

43
00:03:02,724 --> 00:03:05,143
Respecting the privacy of children
is a recent trend.

44
00:03:05,226 --> 00:03:07,812
We are very sophisticated parents.

45
00:03:10,398 --> 00:03:13,151
Goodness. We might never get
to see our child again

46
00:03:13,234 --> 00:03:14,986
if we try to become more sophisticated.

47
00:03:15,737 --> 00:03:18,072
Well, moms who know the passcode
to their children's homes

48
00:03:18,156 --> 00:03:20,366
all end up working like slaves for them.

49
00:03:20,575 --> 00:03:23,328
Gosh, it's better for me
not to see that home

50
00:03:23,411 --> 00:03:24,871
that's messier than a pigpen.

51
00:03:28,166 --> 00:03:30,293
I shouldn't have gotten angry at you.

52
00:03:31,169 --> 00:03:32,629
I was just really taken aback.

53
00:03:34,797 --> 00:03:35,924
I'm sorry.

54
00:03:38,843 --> 00:03:39,928
Are you

55
00:03:41,471 --> 00:03:42,639
angry at me?

56
00:03:43,556 --> 00:03:44,557
Yes.

57
00:03:51,481 --> 00:03:52,607
But...

58
00:03:54,234 --> 00:03:55,443
I'm also sorry

59
00:03:57,654 --> 00:03:59,572
for entering your house
without permission.

60
00:05:07,140 --> 00:05:08,599
Hyo-jin was watching.

61
00:05:15,648 --> 00:05:16,858
Ms. Sung?

62
00:05:17,567 --> 00:05:18,568
Yes?

63
00:05:20,028 --> 00:05:22,280
-Sung Duk-mi.
-Yes?

64
00:05:25,742 --> 00:05:26,784
Mom!

65
00:05:31,039 --> 00:05:32,832
Is that your mother?

66
00:05:35,418 --> 00:05:36,669
Duk-mi!

67
00:05:50,641 --> 00:05:52,852
I'm proud of you, my little girl.

68
00:05:52,935 --> 00:05:54,812
-Proud of what?
-It's nice to meet you.

69
00:05:54,896 --> 00:05:57,482
-I'm the director of Cheum--
-Do you love Duk-mi?

70
00:05:57,565 --> 00:06:00,109
Mom, what are you saying to Director Gold?

71
00:06:00,193 --> 00:06:01,778
You walked her home

72
00:06:01,861 --> 00:06:05,073
and even kissed her in this open space.

73
00:06:05,448 --> 00:06:07,158
It's not what you think.

74
00:06:07,241 --> 00:06:08,618
You must love her a lot.

75
00:06:08,701 --> 00:06:10,536
No, the things is,

76
00:06:10,620 --> 00:06:13,164
Ms. Sung and I work together
at the museum.

77
00:06:13,247 --> 00:06:15,374
Did you fall in love
while working together?

78
00:06:15,458 --> 00:06:17,168
No, we didn't fall in love.

79
00:06:17,251 --> 00:06:19,087
-Have you had dinner?
-No, it's...

80
00:06:19,629 --> 00:06:21,339
Dinner?

81
00:06:22,590 --> 00:06:24,884
You shouldn't skip your meals.

82
00:06:25,176 --> 00:06:26,260
Do you have rice at home?

83
00:06:26,344 --> 00:06:27,637
Home? My home?

84
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:29,263
No, I don't.

85
00:06:31,349 --> 00:06:33,101
We have no choice then. Let's go.

86
00:06:33,184 --> 00:06:34,352
-Sorry?
-Go where?

87
00:06:34,435 --> 00:06:36,270
You said there's no rice at home.

88
00:06:36,354 --> 00:06:38,606
We should at least treat him to dinner.

89
00:06:39,524 --> 00:06:41,609
Mom, there's nothing going on between

90
00:06:41,692 --> 00:06:43,861
-me and--
-Enough said.

91
00:06:44,153 --> 00:06:46,280
Let's go. We have a lot of rice at home

92
00:06:46,364 --> 00:06:48,449
and many side dishes as well.
Let's go then.

93
00:06:48,825 --> 00:06:50,743
Mom, where are you going?

94
00:06:51,119 --> 00:06:54,372
No wonder I suddenly wanted
to cook chicken soup today.

95
00:06:54,455 --> 00:06:56,916
I never imagined running
into you like this.

96
00:06:57,542 --> 00:06:59,794
Do you like hen dish?

97
00:06:59,877 --> 00:07:01,254
Chicken dish?

98
00:07:02,755 --> 00:07:04,340
Sure, I do.

99
00:07:04,549 --> 00:07:05,550
Let's go.

100
00:07:05,883 --> 00:07:08,052
-Wait, what chicken?
-Ms. Sung.

101
00:07:08,970 --> 00:07:12,473
Mom. Are you insane?
Listen to me for a second.

102
00:07:12,557 --> 00:07:13,558
Mom!

103
00:07:46,549 --> 00:07:48,676
Ma'am, can I help you with anything?

104
00:07:48,759 --> 00:07:50,428
No, not at all.

105
00:07:50,511 --> 00:07:52,430
You're our guest. Please sit and relax.

106
00:07:52,513 --> 00:07:53,890
Obviously, he feels uncomfortable.

107
00:07:53,973 --> 00:07:55,600
-Mom, we'll just go.
-Honey,

108
00:07:55,933 --> 00:07:57,935
he must feel uncomfortable because of you.

109
00:07:58,019 --> 00:08:00,271
-Go out, and after ten minutes--
-No!

110
00:08:01,147 --> 00:08:02,273
I feel comfortable.

111
00:08:03,357 --> 00:08:04,942
Just wait a little bit longer.

112
00:08:16,329 --> 00:08:18,122
You must collect viewing stones.

113
00:08:18,664 --> 00:08:19,790
You have a great hobby.

114
00:08:19,874 --> 00:08:22,210
Gosh, it's not a great hobby.

115
00:08:22,293 --> 00:08:24,879
I'm worried that our house might collapse.

116
00:08:41,646 --> 00:08:44,440
In order to fully appreciate the beauty
of its nature,

117
00:08:44,524 --> 00:08:45,900
you must look at it like this.

118
00:08:45,983 --> 00:08:47,527
Do you collect them yourself?

119
00:08:47,610 --> 00:08:48,903
Yes, of course.

120
00:08:48,986 --> 00:08:51,989
I go to all the famous places
when it comes to viewing stones.

121
00:08:52,323 --> 00:08:54,700
-This one is...
-Come and eat.

122
00:08:56,536 --> 00:08:59,497
This one right here portrays the beauty

123
00:08:59,580 --> 00:09:00,998
of landscape scenery.

124
00:09:01,207 --> 00:09:03,376
And of course, how the stone was cut
is very important.

125
00:09:03,459 --> 00:09:06,629
But it's also important to make it
look nice by spraying water on it.

126
00:09:06,879 --> 00:09:09,090
Is he going to speak ten years' worth
of his entire life?

127
00:09:09,173 --> 00:09:10,841
Why is he suddenly so talkative?

128
00:09:10,925 --> 00:09:12,260
Come over already.

129
00:09:12,343 --> 00:09:15,513
And this part is the slope.

130
00:09:16,305 --> 00:09:19,016
This is a stone bottom
along with this on the side.

131
00:09:19,100 --> 00:09:22,603
You need to be able
to use your imagination as you enjoy...

132
00:09:33,447 --> 00:09:35,700
What was your name again?

133
00:09:36,242 --> 00:09:37,285
Ryan...

134
00:09:38,661 --> 00:09:40,037
Ryan Gold, ma'am.

135
00:09:40,329 --> 00:09:41,914
-Are you a foreigner?
-Mom.

136
00:09:43,291 --> 00:09:44,250
Yes.

137
00:09:46,335 --> 00:09:48,879
Your daughter loves a foreigner.

138
00:09:48,963 --> 00:09:51,299
Dating. Luck is coming.

139
00:09:53,092 --> 00:09:54,302
Should I give you some more rice?

140
00:09:54,385 --> 00:09:57,221
I heard it's polite to eat a lot
if someone invites you for a meal.

141
00:09:57,597 --> 00:09:58,723
So I really ate a lot.

142
00:09:58,806 --> 00:10:01,475
-Yes, it was nice to see you eat well.
-Honey.

143
00:10:06,939 --> 00:10:08,733
It was nice to see you enjoy your food.

144
00:10:13,863 --> 00:10:15,489
Mom, we should get going now.

145
00:10:15,573 --> 00:10:17,617
You can't just leave right after you eat.

146
00:10:17,700 --> 00:10:19,368
Yes, she's right.

147
00:10:19,660 --> 00:10:22,204
I have a lot of viewing stones
I want to show you.

148
00:10:22,288 --> 00:10:25,333
I'll show you all sorts
of viewing stones I've collected.

149
00:10:25,541 --> 00:10:27,084
You should have dessert.

150
00:10:27,293 --> 00:10:28,711
It's okay. I don't need dessert.

151
00:10:28,794 --> 00:10:30,838
It's because I want to have dessert.

152
00:10:31,172 --> 00:10:32,632
You guys should wait

153
00:10:32,923 --> 00:10:35,509
in Duk-mi's room and chat a little.

154
00:10:35,593 --> 00:10:37,261
Go where? Mom.

155
00:10:38,137 --> 00:10:41,682
I'll call you once it's ready,
so don't come outside.

156
00:10:42,183 --> 00:10:43,142
Mom.

157
00:10:49,649 --> 00:10:50,608
I'm sorry.

158
00:10:51,776 --> 00:10:52,860
It's okay.

159
00:10:54,403 --> 00:10:55,446
I'm sorry.

160
00:11:02,953 --> 00:11:06,874
You were always so slow.
But why are you suddenly so quick today?

161
00:11:06,957 --> 00:11:08,084
You're so slow-witted.

162
00:11:08,209 --> 00:11:10,711
Let's give them some time
so they can talk.

163
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:21,389
CERTIFICATE OF AWARD
ART CONTEST

164
00:11:21,847 --> 00:11:24,600
THE GRAND PRIZE

165
00:11:30,439 --> 00:11:33,150
Why did you quit art?

166
00:11:35,569 --> 00:11:38,280
My dad may seem like a rock collector,

167
00:11:38,364 --> 00:11:40,866
but back in the days,
his dream was to be a businessman.

168
00:11:42,576 --> 00:11:44,995
I was getting ready to study abroad.

169
00:11:45,538 --> 00:11:48,874
But he made a huge mistake
and lost our family a lot of money.

170
00:11:51,669 --> 00:11:53,838
My mom told me not to be bothered
and that I should just go,

171
00:11:53,921 --> 00:11:55,840
but I couldn't do that. It was obvious

172
00:11:55,923 --> 00:11:58,342
that my family would split apart
if I went abroad.

173
00:12:01,387 --> 00:12:02,596
So I just gave up.

174
00:12:04,932 --> 00:12:07,184
If I did go abroad back then,

175
00:12:07,268 --> 00:12:09,520
I would've met you as an artist

176
00:12:09,603 --> 00:12:11,105
instead of a curator.

177
00:12:12,064 --> 00:12:14,817
I would've been a really fussy artist
just like Ryan Gold.

178
00:12:19,321 --> 00:12:20,322
Are you okay

179
00:12:21,407 --> 00:12:23,033
even though you can't live as an artist?

180
00:12:29,373 --> 00:12:31,333
I feel better after I cry once in a while.

181
00:12:32,418 --> 00:12:34,545
Every time I feel regretful,

182
00:12:35,171 --> 00:12:36,714
I just get really drunk

183
00:12:38,674 --> 00:12:39,592
and cry a lot.

184
00:12:40,009 --> 00:12:41,552
That makes me feel better.

185
00:12:43,012 --> 00:12:45,264
And once that passes by,
some things make me laugh again.

186
00:12:47,183 --> 00:12:49,185
And that sometimes leads me
to become happy again.

187
00:13:06,869 --> 00:13:09,997
-My gosh.
-Gosh, this is annoying.

188
00:13:12,583 --> 00:13:15,211
Editor Nam? What are you doing here?
You didn't even call.

189
00:13:15,294 --> 00:13:17,505
-Apparently, Duk-mi's home and--
-Duk-mi?

190
00:13:17,796 --> 00:13:19,548
-Duk-mi's home?
-Yes.

191
00:13:19,673 --> 00:13:21,467
Why did she not tell me about it?

192
00:13:23,385 --> 00:13:25,304
But what's the big deal
about her coming home?

193
00:13:25,387 --> 00:13:27,389
She brought home the director
of Cheum Museum.

194
00:13:27,765 --> 00:13:29,892
What? She brought that Lion

195
00:13:31,477 --> 00:13:32,937
-to our house?
-Yes.

196
00:13:33,562 --> 00:13:35,564
Is she crazy?

197
00:13:41,737 --> 00:13:44,031
Move. Yeong-suk, it's me.

198
00:13:44,114 --> 00:13:46,283
Goodness, it would've been nice
if you could stay for longer.

199
00:13:49,453 --> 00:13:50,913
How did you guys come together?

200
00:13:50,996 --> 00:13:52,498
We met downstairs.

201
00:13:53,123 --> 00:13:55,584
-Is your guest leaving already?
-Yes.

202
00:13:55,834 --> 00:13:58,045
I kept him here for way too long.

203
00:13:58,921 --> 00:14:00,214
My goodness, I almost forgot.

204
00:14:00,297 --> 00:14:02,091
Don't go yet. Wait here.

205
00:14:03,050 --> 00:14:04,635
Just a second.

206
00:14:05,928 --> 00:14:09,557
Hello, I'm Nam Se-yeon,
the chief editor of Moment,

207
00:14:09,640 --> 00:14:10,891
the art magazine.

208
00:14:13,769 --> 00:14:16,021
I'm Ryan Gold,
the director of Cheum Museum.

209
00:14:18,399 --> 00:14:21,193
Editor Nam, you must be here
to ask him for an interview.

210
00:14:22,194 --> 00:14:24,530
I've been wanting to visit you
at the museum.

211
00:14:24,613 --> 00:14:27,575
But I heard that you're here,
so I came in a hurry to ask you a favor.

212
00:14:27,950 --> 00:14:29,493
I'm not saying this
because I'm close to her.

213
00:14:29,577 --> 00:14:32,037
But it is one of the few good
art magazines in the country.

214
00:14:32,121 --> 00:14:33,455
You should think about it.

215
00:14:33,539 --> 00:14:36,333
Okay, I'll think about it.

216
00:14:36,417 --> 00:14:37,668
Thank you, Director Gold.

217
00:14:38,377 --> 00:14:39,712
Here you go.

218
00:14:39,795 --> 00:14:42,548
I packed a few side dishes
that you seemed to like earlier.

219
00:14:43,215 --> 00:14:44,383
Thank you.

220
00:14:45,843 --> 00:14:47,386
Thank you for this.

221
00:14:48,012 --> 00:14:49,555
-We'll be off now.
-Okay.

222
00:14:49,930 --> 00:14:52,016
-You too?
-Thank you so much for today.

223
00:14:52,349 --> 00:14:54,935
Director Gold, I hope you visit again.

224
00:14:59,607 --> 00:15:01,233
-I'll give you a call.
-Sure.

225
00:15:04,236 --> 00:15:05,362
Mom, I'm hungry!

226
00:15:06,238 --> 00:15:08,282
What? Didn't you eat?

227
00:15:08,657 --> 00:15:11,410
Yeong-suk, stop feeding him.

228
00:15:12,703 --> 00:15:13,787
Bye.

229
00:15:14,330 --> 00:15:15,831
I hope you visit again.

230
00:15:28,344 --> 00:15:31,263
I'm sorry. I didn't know
my parents would be there.

231
00:15:32,181 --> 00:15:33,390
Didn't you feel uncomfortable?

232
00:15:33,599 --> 00:15:37,394
I ate way too much for me to say
that I felt uncomfortable.

233
00:15:37,478 --> 00:15:39,229
I did notice you eating a lot.

234
00:15:43,025 --> 00:15:44,652
I'd like to apologize once again.

235
00:15:45,819 --> 00:15:47,071
I'm sincerely very sorry.

236
00:15:48,364 --> 00:15:49,198
Okay.

237
00:15:50,866 --> 00:15:53,661
And thank you for today.

238
00:16:00,292 --> 00:16:01,460
Go home safely.

239
00:16:15,975 --> 00:16:18,310
"Director Gold." My gosh.

240
00:16:18,978 --> 00:16:20,521
I'm also a director at my studio.

241
00:16:54,930 --> 00:16:56,140
What are you doing here?

242
00:16:56,348 --> 00:16:59,059
Everyone's waiting at home
to congratulate you.

243
00:16:59,560 --> 00:17:02,229
Congratulate me for what?
I didn't even win the gold medal.

244
00:17:02,312 --> 00:17:05,733
Silver medals don't mean anything now
because you've won so many?

245
00:17:06,191 --> 00:17:07,943
I really thought
I'd win the gold medal this time.

246
00:17:09,820 --> 00:17:11,363
This is all because of my name.

247
00:17:11,572 --> 00:17:13,866
She should've named me Geum-gi
which sounds more like gold.

248
00:17:14,116 --> 00:17:16,952
Geum-gi? That's not a bad name.

249
00:17:17,161 --> 00:17:19,413
I'll call you Nam Geum-gi from now on.

250
00:17:19,496 --> 00:17:22,541
How does it sound? Hey, Nam Geum-gi.

251
00:17:24,626 --> 00:17:27,588
Don't say it with my last name.

252
00:17:28,255 --> 00:17:29,214
It sounds a little weird.

253
00:17:29,298 --> 00:17:32,885
Why? It suits you just fine.
Hey, Nam Geum-gi.

254
00:17:42,561 --> 00:17:43,437
Here.

255
00:17:47,149 --> 00:17:48,859
Are you giving it to me as a gold medal?

256
00:17:49,610 --> 00:17:50,944
It's chocolate. Eat it.

257
00:17:59,495 --> 00:18:00,579
You know what?

258
00:18:00,913 --> 00:18:01,747
Know what?

259
00:18:14,676 --> 00:18:15,886
Are you insane?

260
00:18:23,685 --> 00:18:25,479
As long as you keep bringing medals,

261
00:18:25,771 --> 00:18:28,482
you'll be the best judo athlete I know.

