let me sell one.

269
00:18:57,469 --> 00:18:58,637
I need more money for tickets.

270
00:18:58,720 --> 00:18:59,680
-No.
-Why not?

271
00:18:59,763 --> 00:19:00,931
-No way.
-Why not?

272
00:19:01,223 --> 00:19:02,558
-They're mine.
-You're sick of them.

273
00:19:03,934 --> 00:19:05,227
Stop being so cheap.

274
00:19:05,310 --> 00:19:07,062
You said you have a lot of them,
so hand one over.

275
00:19:14,278 --> 00:19:15,779
Be a man and lift it higher.

276
00:19:21,702 --> 00:19:23,412
-We'll be off now.
-Okay.

277
00:19:23,495 --> 00:19:25,831
-You too?
-Thank you so much for today.

278
00:19:46,935 --> 00:19:48,437
My goodness.

279
00:19:51,523 --> 00:19:54,651
What on earth did she pack me?

280
00:20:11,084 --> 00:20:12,252
Freeze the bulgogi

281
00:20:12,336 --> 00:20:15,005
and let it thaw in the fridge
before stir-frying it.

282
00:20:32,022 --> 00:20:34,316
You seemed to enjoy freshly made kimchi,

283
00:20:34,399 --> 00:20:35,692
so I packed a small amount.

284
00:20:35,901 --> 00:20:37,569
Let me know when you run out.

285
00:20:54,127 --> 00:20:56,630
This gwantongseok
is known to help you prosper

286
00:20:56,797 --> 00:20:58,757
and bring you luck.

287
00:20:59,341 --> 00:21:02,636
I wish you the best in everything you do.

288
00:21:04,471 --> 00:21:06,223
I thought it was as heavy as a stone.

289
00:21:07,516 --> 00:21:09,268
Who knew that he had given me one?

290
00:21:17,651 --> 00:21:20,988
Congratulations. You became
a VIP member of The Road to Si-an.

291
00:21:22,698 --> 00:21:23,573
Yes!

292
00:21:57,816 --> 00:21:58,900
What are you doing?

293
00:22:16,752 --> 00:22:18,420
It was his finger, not his lips.

294
00:22:20,130 --> 00:22:21,465
Why were you caught in the moment?

295
00:22:21,548 --> 00:22:23,467
You should've said,
"What do you think you're doing?"

296
00:22:25,886 --> 00:22:28,305
You let your instincts take over
way too easily.

297
00:22:29,431 --> 00:22:30,474
This is so embarrassing.

298
00:23:03,840 --> 00:23:06,051
Hey. What are you still doing up?

299
00:23:06,259 --> 00:23:08,053
I was waiting for you, of course.

300
00:23:08,386 --> 00:23:10,388
Why did you wait?
You're probably exhausted too.

301
00:23:11,807 --> 00:23:13,975
-Do you want some beer?
-Sure.

302
00:23:21,608 --> 00:23:24,194
Did they agree
to let you join the variety show division?

303
00:23:26,446 --> 00:23:28,573
If I successfully wrap up a story,

304
00:23:28,990 --> 00:23:30,200
they'll transfer me.

305
00:23:30,283 --> 00:23:31,368
-Really?
-Yes.

306
00:23:31,451 --> 00:23:33,620
-So what's the story?
-Oh, that.

307
00:23:39,876 --> 00:23:42,379
-Well...
-Don't tell me

308
00:23:43,755 --> 00:23:45,757
-it's about a cult, is it?
-What?

309
00:23:46,341 --> 00:23:48,135
No, of course not.

310
00:23:49,136 --> 00:23:50,470
It's just a story

311
00:23:51,596 --> 00:23:53,557
on those trying very hard in life.

312
00:23:53,640 --> 00:23:56,601
-Good. As long as it's not a cult.
-Right.

313
00:23:57,227 --> 00:23:59,146
-As long as it's not a cult.
-It's just wrong.

314
00:23:59,229 --> 00:24:01,648
No. No cults.

315
00:24:02,941 --> 00:24:04,317
Mom.

316
00:24:09,573 --> 00:24:10,782
Geon-u.

317
00:24:11,908 --> 00:24:13,493
You're in a dream.

318
00:24:14,536 --> 00:24:16,371
You haven't woken up.

319
00:24:17,080 --> 00:24:20,333
Let's go. I am an angel
that only looks like your mom.

320
00:24:35,098 --> 00:24:37,934
His smile couldn't be more vibrant.

321
00:24:41,688 --> 00:24:44,149
His sharp jawline captivated me.

322
00:24:46,151 --> 00:24:47,402
They must be new fans.

323
00:24:49,404 --> 00:24:52,908
"There probably wasn't enough light,
but radial filters were used

324
00:24:52,991 --> 00:24:54,618
to get the maximum out of what they had."

325
00:24:54,701 --> 00:24:57,537
His captured expression
in the form of a medium shot

326
00:24:57,621 --> 00:25:00,123
effectively draws our gaze
to tell the story.

327
00:25:00,207 --> 00:25:01,833
It is truly an impressive photo.

328
00:25:02,250 --> 00:25:04,836
Latte has an eye for photos.

329
00:25:10,300 --> 00:25:12,886
CHEUM MUSEUM OF ART

330
00:25:19,392 --> 00:25:20,810
Latte, thank you.

331
00:25:20,894 --> 00:25:22,896
Compliments and advice are always welcome.

332
00:25:40,288 --> 00:25:41,331
Ms. Kim.

333
00:25:43,792 --> 00:25:44,751
What is it?

334
00:25:50,340 --> 00:25:53,551
Ms. Kim, you're no longer needed
at the museum.

335
00:25:54,552 --> 00:25:55,637
You're fired.

336
00:25:55,720 --> 00:25:57,138
Fired? Why?

337
00:25:58,348 --> 00:26:00,183
Do you want to be sued instead?

338
00:26:00,267 --> 00:26:01,643
You choose between the two.

339
00:26:02,394 --> 00:26:04,562
-What will you sue me for?
-Stalking.

340
00:26:04,813 --> 00:26:07,440
You saw me at Ms. Sung's house last night.

341
00:26:16,700 --> 00:26:18,451
I think you're mistaken.

342
00:26:20,620 --> 00:26:23,581
I found something interesting online.

343
00:26:24,165 --> 00:26:25,375
CUPATCH.

344
00:26:27,585 --> 00:26:29,671
-What's that?
-The work of the one I'll sue.

345
00:26:29,754 --> 00:26:31,589
Why am I the only one you're suing?

346
00:26:31,840 --> 00:26:33,049
Is that a confession?

347
00:26:34,426 --> 00:26:37,595
Why aren't you suing The Road to Si-an?
She also stalked you too.

348
00:26:38,346 --> 00:26:39,764
You're working with her, aren't you?

349
00:26:40,807 --> 00:26:42,309
I'll sue you both.

350
00:26:45,979 --> 00:26:47,314
I'll delete it then.

351
00:26:51,401 --> 00:26:52,736
I'll be watching.

352
00:26:58,199 --> 00:26:59,200
No way!

353
00:27:07,792 --> 00:27:11,338
WINNERS OF CHA SI-AN'S SIGNING EVENT

354
00:27:16,426 --> 00:27:17,427
-No way.
-My gosh.

355
00:27:17,761 --> 00:27:18,845
Is something wrong?

356
00:27:18,928 --> 00:27:21,806
I won a spot at Si-an's signing event.

357
00:27:22,724 --> 00:27:23,892
Congratulations.

358
00:27:24,768 --> 00:27:27,771
I knew I was going.
I'm talking about The Road to Si-an.

359
00:27:30,231 --> 00:27:31,441
THE ROAD TO SI-AN

360
00:27:31,524 --> 00:27:33,443
I gave up on this signing event
which is why I posted

361
00:27:33,526 --> 00:27:35,612
on social media that I had bought
one copy of the album.

362
00:27:35,695 --> 00:27:36,988
-But you won a spot.
-This is...

363
00:27:37,072 --> 00:27:38,448
Destiny.

364
00:27:43,870 --> 00:27:46,414
I bought a whole box of his albums
to win a spot at the event,

365
00:27:46,623 --> 00:27:47,916
but she got in with a single copy.

366
00:27:48,416 --> 00:27:51,711
She'll probably babble on
about it being fate.

367
00:27:53,838 --> 00:27:55,840
When is that signing event?

368
00:27:56,466 --> 00:27:57,884
Next week on the day the museum closes.

369
00:27:57,967 --> 00:27:59,719
I wouldn't play hooky to attend it.

370
00:28:05,642 --> 00:28:07,644
So The Road to Si-an
will be coming as well.

371
00:28:13,691 --> 00:28:16,194
That duchess fortune-teller
is really impressive.

372
00:28:16,986 --> 00:28:19,489
She said Duk-mi would bring home
some foreign guy,

373
00:28:19,572 --> 00:28:21,116
and she eventually brought Ryan.

374
00:28:21,658 --> 00:28:24,744
We should speak simple English
in case we meet his parents.

375
00:28:24,828 --> 00:28:26,746
-You should study with me.
-Okay.

376
00:28:33,044 --> 00:28:35,338
-This means "our son-in-law."
-Our son-in-law.

377
00:28:35,422 --> 00:28:36,423
Si-an.

378
00:28:37,715 --> 00:28:39,050
Si-an.

379
00:28:39,509 --> 00:28:42,262
-Our son-in-law.
-Our son-in-law.

380
00:28:45,807 --> 00:28:47,892
-Our son-in-law.
-Our son-in-law.

381
00:28:48,059 --> 00:28:49,185
Congratulations, Duk-mi.

382
00:28:49,728 --> 00:28:50,979
It's all thanks to you.

383
00:28:51,521 --> 00:28:53,189
-Our son-in-law.
-Our son-in-law.

384
00:28:53,273 --> 00:28:55,942
Si-an.

385
00:28:57,152 --> 00:28:59,195
-Our son-in-law.
-Our son-in-law.

