00:57:12,137 --> 00:57:14,347
-You must not open them.
-Okay.

777
00:57:14,430 --> 00:57:15,515
I'm going in.

778
00:57:17,392 --> 00:57:20,895
This may feel uncomfortable,
but it'll just take a second.

779
00:57:27,819 --> 00:57:29,737
All right, follow me now.

780
00:57:30,405 --> 00:57:31,448
This way.

781
00:57:32,157 --> 00:57:33,950
I'll bring you the acetone.

782
00:57:37,328 --> 00:57:39,414
The couch is over here. Come this way.

783
00:57:39,497 --> 00:57:40,540
Ms. Sung.

784
00:57:42,375 --> 00:57:45,795
How messy is your house,
for goodness sake?

785
00:57:51,759 --> 00:57:54,554
You might faint if you see it.

786
00:58:09,068 --> 00:58:10,069
Is it coming off?

787
00:58:10,403 --> 00:58:12,363
Yes, I'm glad it's coming off.

788
00:58:15,408 --> 00:58:17,118
I smelled paint from your room.

789
00:58:17,494 --> 00:58:18,912
Do you still paint these days?

790
00:58:22,582 --> 00:58:23,541
Sometimes.

791
00:58:29,506 --> 00:58:31,216
I always wanted to ask you this.

792
00:58:31,466 --> 00:58:32,425
What is it?

793
00:58:33,384 --> 00:58:35,345
When you couldn't draw

794
00:58:36,054 --> 00:58:37,347
because your arm was broken.

795
00:58:41,184 --> 00:58:42,602
How did you stand it?

796
00:58:54,572 --> 00:58:56,157
I used my left hand.

797
00:58:56,324 --> 00:58:57,325
Left hand?

798
00:58:58,034 --> 00:58:59,619
I'm right-handed.

799
00:59:00,119 --> 00:59:03,873
Since I couldn't use my right hand,
I drew with my left hand.

800
00:59:03,998 --> 00:59:06,668
Were you able to draw
as well as you did with your right hand

801
00:59:06,751 --> 00:59:08,002
using your left hand then?

802
00:59:09,921 --> 00:59:12,674
No. I was terrible at drawing
with my left hand.

803
00:59:16,094 --> 00:59:17,178
But it was fun.

804
00:59:18,388 --> 00:59:21,599
I felt so pressured
that I had to draw well before

805
00:59:22,016 --> 00:59:23,393
so I couldn't enjoy it.

806
00:59:23,851 --> 00:59:25,562
But when I drew with my left hand,

807
00:59:26,563 --> 00:59:27,897
I had so much fun.

808
00:59:27,981 --> 00:59:29,691
It was like scribbling when I was a kid.

809
00:59:40,326 --> 00:59:41,244
There you go.

810
00:59:42,829 --> 00:59:45,331
-Thank you.
-This was my fault anyway.

811
00:59:47,584 --> 00:59:49,127
Come to think of it,

812
00:59:49,711 --> 00:59:51,045
this feels unfair.

813
00:59:51,713 --> 00:59:52,839
What is?

814
00:59:53,548 --> 00:59:55,258
You saw my whole house.

815
00:59:56,009 --> 00:59:57,552
But why can't I see yours?

816
00:59:59,929 --> 01:00:02,265
To make things fair, I'll look too.

817
01:00:02,890 --> 01:00:04,017
No!

818
01:00:24,871 --> 01:00:26,748
I feel totally fine.

819
01:00:32,378 --> 01:00:33,713
I must be confident

820
01:00:37,467 --> 01:00:38,885
and be true to my feelings.

821
01:00:49,771 --> 01:00:51,064
I shall choose you.

822
01:00:58,946 --> 01:01:00,448
I will give you the honor

823
01:01:04,535 --> 01:01:05,662
to kiss me.

824
01:01:40,613 --> 01:01:42,532
Do you want to keep pretending
that you're dating?

825
01:01:42,782 --> 01:01:44,659
If she does and he refuses,

826
01:01:44,867 --> 01:01:46,661
she might even lose him as a friend.

827
01:01:46,786 --> 01:01:49,622
I want to stay by Ryan and work with him.

828
01:01:49,956 --> 01:01:51,374
I like Ryan.

829
01:01:51,874 --> 01:01:53,668
The thing is, Director Gold...

830
01:01:53,751 --> 01:01:55,294
-I...
-Duk-mi!

831
01:01:55,378 --> 01:01:56,963
Date a guy who you can tell honestly

832
01:01:57,046 --> 01:01:59,424
that you're a fangirl for life.

833
01:01:59,590 --> 01:02:01,384
People might think you're really jealous.

834
01:02:01,551 --> 01:02:03,219
When was I jealous?

835
01:02:04,053 --> 01:02:05,304
I like you.

836
01:02:06,013 --> 01:02:07,140
I really do.

837
01:02:07,348 --> 01:02:10,268
Subtitle translation by Seul-ki Kim

